{
  "doc_id": "30634",
  "text": "The predominance of the CTX-M-gene family among the ESBL genes in Dutch isolates has also been observed in Belgium, France, Italy, Poland, Spain and Canada. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] As in the Netherlands, CTX-M-15 was most prevalent within the CTX-M family in all these countries, except in Poland and Spain were CTX-M-3 and CTX-M-14 were more prevalent. [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
